WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.500
Naturally, since the main task for the rotor is behavior prediction,

00:06.500 --> 00:15.500
the rotor, based on the requirements of the natural scientific description,

00:15.500 --> 00:22.000
offers a formula that allows this behavior prediction to be built.

00:22.000 --> 00:26.500
So, from the point of view of the rotor, behavior prediction is a potential.

00:26.500 --> 00:31.500
The desire and the requirements that I set for myself.

00:31.500 --> 00:37.500
And this potential of behavior is made up of expectations,

00:37.500 --> 00:42.000
again, I set for myself, and those values and reinforcements that I have

00:42.000 --> 00:46.500
from the point of view and with respect to social values.

00:46.500 --> 00:52.500
If I know, measure, represent the expectations of a person,

00:52.500 --> 00:58.500
if I know his attitude, his assessment, his representation,

00:58.500 --> 01:06.500
the values chosen by him, then I can assess the potential that he can achieve.

01:06.500 --> 01:09.500
Again, the idea is very simple.

01:09.500 --> 01:11.500
Let's take a careerist.

01:11.500 --> 01:16.500
At the moment when he is busy to achieve promotion,

01:16.500 --> 01:21.500
he works overtime, he re-executes plans.

01:21.500 --> 01:32.500
He is active, but he does it not to increase the company's performance,

01:32.500 --> 01:34.500
not to take care of the company.

01:34.500 --> 01:38.500
He has only one value, to be promoted.

01:38.500 --> 01:43.500
His expectations are connected with his promotion.

01:43.500 --> 01:48.500
If these expectations coincide with the value of the reinforcement,

01:48.500 --> 01:52.500
then he gets a promotion, and here is the potential.

01:52.500 --> 01:55.500
We can predict that he has achieved his goal.

01:55.500 --> 02:01.500
If there is a discrepancy in expectations and values,

02:01.500 --> 02:04.500
then the total amount may be insufficient,

02:04.500 --> 02:09.500
and, in the end, the attitude to you as a careerist

02:09.500 --> 02:16.500
may be the reason for not promoting you to the management position.

02:16.500 --> 02:19.500
You have already quarreled with the team,

02:19.500 --> 02:22.500
so you will scold everyone if you are still in power.

02:22.500 --> 02:24.500
Here is the potential of his behavior.

02:24.500 --> 02:28.500
And, knowing the expectations, values and reinforcement,

02:28.500 --> 02:30.500
I can make predictions.

02:30.500 --> 02:33.500
It is not necessary that my prediction will be fulfilled.

02:33.500 --> 02:35.500
Will it be fulfilled or not,

02:35.500 --> 02:38.500
I will see it in my experience and practice.

02:38.500 --> 02:41.500
If it will not be fulfilled, then I made a mistake somewhere.

02:41.500 --> 02:46.500
I am given a formula that can serve as a prognostic interest.

02:46.500 --> 02:51.500
This is what concerns the theory of social learning of Rotor.

02:51.500 --> 02:53.500
But Rotor is not a data-driven company.

02:53.500 --> 02:58.500
The advantage of biheorists is that they are operational.

02:58.500 --> 03:03.500
They do not build theories that can be tested,

03:03.500 --> 03:05.500
argued and written in dissertations.

03:05.500 --> 03:09.500
They build an experiment that can be carried out

03:09.500 --> 03:12.500
and it will give an answer whether you are right or not.

03:12.500 --> 03:15.500
If we talk about social prognosis,

03:15.500 --> 03:24.500
then, of course, there are some motives that move a person towards a goal.

03:24.500 --> 03:27.500
There are some motives that he wants to satisfy.

03:27.500 --> 03:33.500
In this case, Rotor introduces the concept of necessity.

03:33.500 --> 03:38.500
It has long been seen in psychology, but not in biheorism.

03:38.500 --> 03:40.500
Biheorists did not need necessity,

03:40.500 --> 03:43.500
because necessity was in the inner characteristics.

03:43.500 --> 03:46.500
This is for cognitivists, this is for general psychologists.

03:46.500 --> 03:51.500
Rotor introduces a biheoristic, a biheral understanding of necessity.

03:51.500 --> 03:58.500
Necessity as specific goals that I need to achieve.

03:58.500 --> 04:03.500
These are the same expectations that I strive for from the previous formula.

04:04.500 --> 04:06.500
But again, it is not enough to introduce.

04:06.500 --> 04:10.500
We need to give a way to measure these needs,

04:10.500 --> 04:15.500
understood as specific goals that I strive for.

04:15.500 --> 04:22.500
Rotor solves this problem by introducing six main criteria

04:22.500 --> 04:25.500
that characterize human needs.

04:25.500 --> 04:29.500
Moreover, these criteria characterize these needs

04:29.500 --> 04:32.500
from the point of view of a person's behavior prognosis.

04:32.500 --> 04:35.500
For Rotor, the main task is prognosis.

04:35.500 --> 04:40.500
What a person will do, how he will behave.

04:40.500 --> 04:43.500
But in order to answer the question, how,

04:43.500 --> 04:46.500
I need to know why and what points he does.

04:46.500 --> 04:53.500
As for these categories, the first category is the status of recognition.

04:53.500 --> 04:56.500
A person is a social being.

04:56.500 --> 05:02.500
If I try to achieve a certain position, a certain social niche,

05:02.500 --> 05:09.500
it is determined by the social hierarchy that is created by the society.

05:09.500 --> 05:12.500
This is the social recognition theory of Rotor.

05:12.500 --> 05:17.500
Accordingly, this niche has a certain status.

05:17.500 --> 05:23.500
One thing is to be a janitor, another thing is to be a president.

05:23.500 --> 05:28.500
The third thing is to be a general director.

05:28.500 --> 05:32.500
The fourth thing is to be a project manager, and so on.

05:32.500 --> 05:34.500
There are certain statuses.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.500
Depending on what status you are,

05:37.500 --> 05:40.500
depending on what status you strive for,

05:40.500 --> 05:42.500
it depends on your expectations.

05:42.500 --> 05:47.500
You can strive to be the senior assistant of the second junior janitor.

05:47.500 --> 05:49.500
This is your status.

05:49.500 --> 05:56.500
This is the level of achievements that you have set for yourself.

05:56.500 --> 05:58.500
This is your reputation.

05:58.500 --> 06:09.500
The status of a teacher, doctor, lawyer, economist, teacher, businessman is different.

06:09.500 --> 06:17.500
Every social role has its own social status.

06:17.500 --> 06:23.500
When you choose a certain role, you set a bar for yourself.

06:23.500 --> 06:26.500
A bar is the level of your expectations.

06:26.500 --> 06:32.500
The higher the status of recognition, the higher the level of your expectations.

06:32.500 --> 06:40.500
But, naturally, we live in a social world, as Rotor claims.

06:40.500 --> 06:45.500
Unfortunately, not everything depends on me.

06:45.500 --> 06:47.500
Yes, a person has an activity.

06:47.500 --> 06:49.500
Rotor does not argue with Bandura.

06:49.500 --> 06:53.500
Rotor and Bandura are representatives of the cognitive-behavioral direction,

06:53.500 --> 06:55.500
and a person is active for them.

06:55.500 --> 06:57.500
Here they are divided into radical behaviorism.

06:57.500 --> 07:05.500
But the problem is that a person understands

07:05.500 --> 07:12.500
that other people claim the same niche in the social ladder.

07:12.500 --> 07:14.500
There are many of them.

07:14.500 --> 07:20.500
Consequently, there is a certain struggle,

07:20.500 --> 07:24.500
the outcome of which is not clear.

07:24.500 --> 07:29.500
Therefore, you need to have some protection.

07:29.500 --> 07:31.500
Protection for yourself,

07:31.500 --> 07:37.500
because not everyone will be able to become a janitor, if desired.

07:37.500 --> 07:43.500
In this regard, I must have some protection for my inner variables,

07:43.500 --> 07:45.500
for my activity,

07:45.500 --> 07:51.500
which will allow me to maintain my self-esteem

07:51.500 --> 07:55.500
in case of not achieving the desired status.

07:55.500 --> 07:59.500
To maintain the very effectiveness that Bandura talks about.

07:59.500 --> 08:04.500
Rotor understands perfectly well that if a person's self-esteem drops,

08:04.500 --> 08:10.500
his inner variables are under threat,

08:10.500 --> 08:13.500
and they begin to depend on external stimuli.

08:13.500 --> 08:19.500
We move from the new formula of stimulus of the inner variable reaction

08:19.500 --> 08:21.500
to the old one, stimulus of the reaction.

08:21.500 --> 08:23.500
Inner variables are devalued.

08:23.500 --> 08:28.500
Why should I deal with them if I still can't achieve anything?

08:28.500 --> 08:32.500
A person again becomes dependent on the external world.

08:32.500 --> 08:34.500
From the point of view of the rotor,

08:34.500 --> 08:40.500
a person must find his place in this world

08:40.500 --> 08:44.500
depending on the conditions that surround him.

08:44.500 --> 08:50.500
In this regard, the next category that he highlights is the category of domination.

08:50.500 --> 08:53.500
People have different expectations.

08:53.500 --> 08:58.500
Someone wants to rise to have power.

08:58.500 --> 09:01.500
It doesn't matter why, it doesn't matter why.

09:01.500 --> 09:05.500
I have an expectation that I must be above someone,

09:05.500 --> 09:08.500
that is, someone must be in my power.

09:08.500 --> 09:15.500
If I can't dominate, then I am in someone's power.

09:15.500 --> 09:20.500
And, accordingly, the level of my pressures falls.

09:20.500 --> 09:23.500
I begin to justify myself.

09:23.500 --> 09:25.500
Why do I need extra responsibility?

09:25.500 --> 09:27.500
Why do I need headaches and so on?

09:27.500 --> 09:30.500
I think this is more than justified to maintain one's self-esteem.

09:30.500 --> 09:37.500
Therefore, domination is an important criterion that determines the power of a person's activity.

09:37.500 --> 09:40.500
Strong domination, I will go on headaches.

09:40.500 --> 09:45.500
Weak domination, they wouldn't touch me.

09:45.500 --> 09:47.500
The rules of the tram.

09:47.500 --> 09:52.500
The fourth indicator is independence.

09:52.500 --> 09:55.500
Naturally, all these indicators are interconnected.

09:55.500 --> 10:02.500
The schemes proposed by Skinner, Bandura, Rotter,

10:02.500 --> 10:07.500
are autonomous indicators that exist independently of each other.

10:07.500 --> 10:10.500
All these indicators are interconnected.

10:10.500 --> 10:14.500
This is a system, which is very good, which is very important in Bichiarism.

10:14.500 --> 10:18.500
They create autonomy, they create a system of parameters.

10:18.500 --> 10:24.500
And this is the criterion that is included in the methodology of Bichiarism.

10:24.500 --> 10:26.500
Independence.

10:26.500 --> 10:35.500
Am I ready to take responsibility for my reaction, for my behavior,

10:35.500 --> 10:42.500
for processing my internal variables of these external requirements?

10:42.500 --> 10:47.500
The manager works in the company, he receives the task,

10:47.500 --> 10:53.500
and then he, at his own risk, comes up with different ways to solve it.

10:53.500 --> 10:58.500
He can solve everything and get a promotion, a bonus, a promotion.

10:58.500 --> 11:02.500
He may not take something into account, not fulfill the plan,

11:02.500 --> 11:05.500
receive a fine, dismissal, punishment.

11:05.500 --> 11:12.500
So, independence is, in fact, the degree of responsibility.

11:12.500 --> 11:16.500
How much responsibility can I take?

11:16.500 --> 11:19.500
The more domination, the more responsibility I am ready to take.

11:20.500 --> 11:23.500
The more responsibility I take, the higher the status I claim.

11:23.500 --> 11:29.500
The more responsibility I take, the more dependent I am on circumstances,

11:29.500 --> 11:33.500
because I am responsible for too many points.

11:33.500 --> 11:44.500
The next criterion is, again, for Bichiarism, an unacceptable one.

11:44.500 --> 11:46.500
Love and attachment.

11:46.500 --> 11:49.500
How can you measure love and attachment?

11:49.500 --> 11:52.500
The situation is very simple.

11:52.500 --> 11:55.500
How many people love you?

11:55.500 --> 11:58.500
How many people do you love?

11:58.500 --> 12:04.500
Love is understood here as a measure of trust.

12:04.500 --> 12:07.500
How many people can rely on you?

12:07.500 --> 12:10.500
How many people can rely on you?

12:10.500 --> 12:12.500
Love and attachment.

12:12.500 --> 12:16.500
In fact, in this case, we are talking about friends,

12:16.500 --> 12:21.500
about those with whom you have a cooperative relationship,

12:21.500 --> 12:24.500
where the relationship is not a one-on-one,

12:24.500 --> 12:26.500
but a relationship where there is a problem,

12:26.500 --> 12:29.500
I will help you solve it, and I will not take anything from you now.

12:29.500 --> 12:34.500
At the same time, I know that if I have difficulties, you will help me.

12:34.500 --> 12:38.500
For Bichiarism, this is a completely subjective indicator.

12:38.500 --> 12:42.500
But Rotor again introduces love and attachment,

12:42.500 --> 12:44.500
albeit in such a formalized form,

12:44.500 --> 12:48.500
but it is trying to describe a living, functioning,

12:48.500 --> 12:53.500
everyday person existing in the world around us.

12:53.500 --> 13:00.500
And perhaps the most indisputable criterion,

13:00.500 --> 13:03.500
but at the same time difficult to measure, is physical comfort.

13:03.500 --> 13:05.500
We all strive for physical comfort,

13:05.500 --> 13:08.500
but for some people comfort is a dacha in Hawaii,

13:08.500 --> 13:12.500
for others comfort is to get into a corner and just sleep.

13:12.500 --> 13:16.500
For some people comfort is to be brought to the plane,

13:16.500 --> 13:19.500
for another person to fly,

13:19.500 --> 13:21.500
for others comfort is to be left alone,

13:21.500 --> 13:25.500
so that you can relax on the computer.

13:25.500 --> 13:32.500
In this case, physical comfort is measured from the point of view of a person's satisfaction.

13:33.500 --> 13:38.500
Physical, material, tangible stimuli that you have.

13:38.500 --> 13:41.500
And in this regard, this is a Bichiarist approach,

13:41.500 --> 13:48.500
because it is determined by your expectations, your goals,

13:48.500 --> 13:56.500
your independence, your domination, your status of recognition.

13:57.500 --> 14:02.500
It is not necessary that there are direct or inverse proportional connections.

14:02.500 --> 14:07.500
The problem is that a person, as an active being,

14:07.500 --> 14:11.500
can list the necessary conditions for his comfort.

14:11.500 --> 14:16.500
Here, of course, the food, warmth, clothing,

14:16.500 --> 14:20.500
what is called vital needs, if we take, for example, Maslow,

14:20.500 --> 14:23.500
but this is a broader concept.

14:24.500 --> 14:28.500
There are necessities that are necessary for your existence.

14:28.500 --> 14:41.500
And there are conditions of well-being that make your life more satisfying.

14:43.500 --> 14:49.500
In addition to the fact that Rotor considers these six categories of needs,

14:49.500 --> 14:52.500
he understands that the need is a very broad concept.

14:52.500 --> 14:59.500
And in this regard, if I want to operationalize this concept,

14:59.500 --> 15:05.500
to make it measurable, I must introduce some other measurable coefficients.

15:05.500 --> 15:11.500
Therefore, he divides the needs into three components.

15:11.500 --> 15:14.500
In addition to the six categories that we just talked about,

15:14.500 --> 15:19.500
he divides all the needs of a person into three components.

15:19.500 --> 15:21.500
The first component is the potential of need.

15:21.500 --> 15:28.500
That is, the results that I want to achieve.

15:28.500 --> 15:31.500
The need is why I behave this way.

15:31.500 --> 15:36.500
The potential is why I set these tasks for myself.

15:36.500 --> 15:41.500
Again, I can set myself a problem of physical comfort

15:42.500 --> 15:48.500
in terms of potential of need, like a summer cottage, a car, a plane, a yacht,

15:48.500 --> 15:50.500
a vacation in Courchevel, and so on.

15:50.500 --> 15:54.500
I can set myself a problem of physical comfort,

15:54.500 --> 15:59.500
like going to a wilderness, not even to a village, but to the woods,

15:59.500 --> 16:02.500
so that no one is there, and to be alone for a week,

16:02.500 --> 16:09.500
without phones, without computers, just you and nature,

16:09.500 --> 16:11.500
and so that there are no people around.

16:11.500 --> 16:16.500
Again, each person sets the potential of his needs.

16:16.500 --> 16:21.500
Moreover, the potential of this need depends on the social environment,

16:21.500 --> 16:27.500
on the tasks that arise in society.

16:27.500 --> 16:33.500
If I have something superfluous, I am ready to get rid of it,

16:33.500 --> 16:37.500
even with the loss of the usual physical comfort.

16:38.500 --> 16:44.500
In addition to the potential of need, Rotor also introduces the value of need.

16:44.500 --> 16:47.500
Look, again, the value.

16:47.500 --> 16:52.500
It has already been in the theory of social learning as the value of reinforcement.

16:52.500 --> 16:55.500
The value in this case again reflects the subjectivity.

16:55.500 --> 17:02.500
It is an assessment of the need that I want to achieve.

17:02.500 --> 17:07.500
And the assessment of others, my social environment of this need.

17:07.500 --> 17:16.500
For example, I can invest all my money to buy a work of art.

17:16.500 --> 17:27.500
At the same time, for example, my country house burned down,

17:27.500 --> 17:30.500
my wife left, I am not interested in that.

17:30.500 --> 17:36.500
I invest all my money in a work of art, so that it is hanging on the wall, and so on.

17:36.500 --> 17:38.500
And everything else is secondary.

17:38.500 --> 17:41.500
I have set my values and needs.

17:41.500 --> 17:47.500
They can be socially acceptable or socially unacceptable.

17:47.500 --> 17:49.500
This is the second question.

17:49.500 --> 17:51.500
The activity comes from a person,

17:51.500 --> 17:57.500
and I subjectively set the desires and needs that I have.

17:58.500 --> 18:01.500
And the third component, again, is very interesting.

18:01.500 --> 18:06.500
All these three components, potential of need, value of need,

18:06.500 --> 18:13.500
they are aimed at revealing the subjectivity of a person.

18:13.500 --> 18:18.500
Subjectivity is like those internal variables that he has.

18:18.500 --> 18:24.500
So, the next component is the freedom of activity and minimally set goals.

18:25.500 --> 18:31.500
In fact, this component reflects the situation that,

18:31.500 --> 18:38.500
being a social being, a person is not free in his actions.

18:38.500 --> 18:44.500
If we walk down the street and see that McDonald's is selling hamburgers,

18:44.500 --> 18:48.500
and we are hungry, we want to eat, we are happy to eat hamburgers,

18:48.500 --> 18:51.500
but suddenly it is discovered that we have no money with us,

18:51.500 --> 18:54.500
and we have a card that is not served in McDonald's,

18:54.500 --> 18:57.500
then our freedom is limited.

18:57.500 --> 19:01.500
Here is a hamburger, but you cannot take it,

19:01.500 --> 19:05.500
because there are certain social requirements,

19:05.500 --> 19:08.500
that you can buy it, and you can buy it for money,

19:08.500 --> 19:10.500
but you don't have it now.

19:10.500 --> 19:17.500
And it turns out that, although you can take one step to satisfy your needs,

19:17.500 --> 19:25.500
you cannot do it, simply because you don't have the necessary components

19:25.500 --> 19:28.500
to achieve this step.

19:28.500 --> 19:34.500
In this regard, when Rotter talks about freedom of activity,

19:34.500 --> 19:37.500
he introduces the concept of minimal goal.

19:37.500 --> 19:39.500
In fact, we have already talked about this.

19:39.500 --> 19:43.500
Each person sets his own level of commitments,

19:43.500 --> 19:49.500
and in this regard there are high, lofty, ideal goals,

19:49.500 --> 19:53.500
which I want to achieve,

19:53.500 --> 19:59.500
but there are those minimal goals that I have to achieve.

19:59.500 --> 20:04.500
I may want to be the general director,

20:04.500 --> 20:08.500
but it didn't work out, it doesn't matter why.

20:08.500 --> 20:12.500
Is it my fault, or the circumstances?

20:12.500 --> 20:18.500
But my minimal goal is to become the head of the department.

20:18.500 --> 20:21.500
Yes, even if I didn't go to the company at 30,

20:21.500 --> 20:24.500
but still I became the head.

20:24.500 --> 20:27.500
Yes, it didn't work out to become the general director,

20:27.500 --> 20:32.500
I will find an excuse, and, accordingly, I will reduce the value,

20:32.500 --> 20:34.500
I will change the efficiency,

20:34.500 --> 20:37.500
but if the minimal goal is not achieved,

20:37.500 --> 20:42.500
then it is a collapse of the human efficiency,

20:42.500 --> 20:45.500
and, accordingly, in this situation,

20:45.500 --> 20:54.500
there is a need to achieve this goal in one way or another.

20:54.500 --> 20:57.500
My freedom is limited by other people,

20:57.500 --> 21:02.500
but other people present an opportunity to achieve at least one goal.

21:02.500 --> 21:04.500
If I don't achieve this goal,

21:04.500 --> 21:07.500
even if I don't become the head of the department,

21:07.500 --> 21:09.500
if I don't achieve the minimal goal,

21:09.500 --> 21:11.500
then I will become a despot in the family.

21:11.500 --> 21:13.500
Even if my wife suffers,

21:13.500 --> 21:15.500
I will have children,

21:15.500 --> 21:17.500
I will quarrel with my mother-in-law,

21:17.500 --> 21:25.500
I somehow managed to imitate the fact that I became the head.

21:25.500 --> 21:28.500
Nobody in my family wants to talk to me,

21:28.500 --> 21:31.500
they don't want to contact me.

21:31.500 --> 21:35.500
But I achieved that goal for myself,

21:35.500 --> 21:37.500
I gave it an assessment,

21:37.500 --> 21:42.500
and my efficiency was saved by the assessment along with it.

21:42.500 --> 21:44.500
In this regard,

21:44.500 --> 21:51.500
the Rotor, after introducing categories and three components of the needs,

21:51.500 --> 21:56.500
clarifies its original formula of behavior prognosis,

21:56.500 --> 21:58.500
and before it, I remind you,

21:58.500 --> 22:02.500
there is a task in the theory of social decision-making to build a behavior prognosis.

22:02.500 --> 22:09.500
It now says that if earlier the potential of behavior was in the sum of expectations and values of reinforcement,

22:09.500 --> 22:13.500
now I introduce new components

22:13.500 --> 22:23.500
that allow me to reduce the breakdown of concepts

22:23.500 --> 22:27.500
and simplify the measurement procedure.

22:27.500 --> 22:33.500
Now it considers that the general formula of the needs prognosis

22:33.500 --> 22:41.500
is that the potential of the needs is equal to the sum of the freedom of activity and the value of the needs.

22:41.500 --> 22:46.500
Look, earlier the formula was expectations plus the value of reinforcement.

22:47.500 --> 22:50.500
A wide breakdown of information,

22:50.500 --> 22:54.500
based on the four variables previously introduced by the Rotor.

22:54.500 --> 22:59.500
Now, after adding six more categories of needs to these four variables,

22:59.500 --> 23:01.500
plus three components of the needs,

23:01.500 --> 23:05.500
it introduces the concept of freedom of activity as

23:05.500 --> 23:08.500
freedom of activity is my activity,

23:08.500 --> 23:13.500
but my activity is limited by the social environment that exists.

23:13.500 --> 23:17.500
There are not many local social ladders,

23:17.500 --> 23:19.500
there are a lot of applicants.

23:19.500 --> 23:22.500
All this limits my freedom,

