49:25.500 --> 49:28.500
the consequence of which is behavior.

49:28.500 --> 49:30.500
From the point of view of Kelly,

49:30.500 --> 49:34.500
human activity is determined,

49:34.500 --> 49:39.500
guided by the ways in which he predicts events.

49:39.500 --> 49:41.500
It's a simple thought.

49:41.500 --> 49:43.500
Any person, researcher,

49:43.500 --> 49:46.500
subjective scientist, ordinary scientist,

49:46.500 --> 49:48.500
why does he study this world?

49:48.500 --> 49:53.500
He studies this world in order to make it predictable.

49:53.500 --> 49:55.500
Only in that world I feel comfortable,

49:55.500 --> 49:57.500
only in that world I feel calm,

49:57.500 --> 49:59.500
where I know what to expect,

49:59.500 --> 50:02.500
where I know what problems may occur,

50:02.500 --> 50:05.500
what circumstances may arise,

50:05.500 --> 50:07.500
where I know what's behind the corner,

50:07.500 --> 50:10.500
where I know that no one will attack me from behind.

50:10.500 --> 50:12.500
That's a simple thought.

50:12.500 --> 50:14.500
And really, judge for yourself,

50:14.500 --> 50:19.500
I don't think this postulate will cause a lot of disputes.

50:19.500 --> 50:22.500
We feel calm in the usual environment.

50:22.500 --> 50:23.500
Why?

50:23.500 --> 50:25.500
Because we know everything there.

50:25.500 --> 50:27.500
We may not like it,

50:27.500 --> 50:29.500
we may not be satisfied,

50:29.500 --> 50:31.500
but we feel calm there,

50:31.500 --> 50:35.500
because we know where, who, what, where to expect what.

50:35.500 --> 50:40.500
If a person finds himself in a new situation,

50:40.500 --> 50:44.500
there's no need to necessarily go to an extreme situation.

50:44.500 --> 50:47.500
A person went to the subway station,

50:47.500 --> 50:50.500
where he had never been before.

50:50.500 --> 50:56.500
And suddenly he decided to buy a pie or something else in a kiosk.

50:56.500 --> 50:58.500
Something he hadn't done before.

50:58.500 --> 51:03.500
Naturally, a person already has certain expectations.

51:03.500 --> 51:05.500
What can be waiting for him?

51:05.500 --> 51:07.500
That the pie may not be fried,

51:07.500 --> 51:09.500
that there may be a confection,

51:09.500 --> 51:12.500
that these pies are made from a dog, and so on.

51:12.500 --> 51:14.500
That is, he is already...

51:14.500 --> 51:17.500
After all, a person is not Robinson.

51:17.500 --> 51:20.500
He lives in this world, in this social environment.

51:20.500 --> 51:23.500
And naturally, living in this environment,

51:23.500 --> 51:27.500
he is interested in making himself comfortable in this environment.

51:27.500 --> 51:31.500
He will be comfortable only if he has information

51:31.500 --> 51:34.500
about what is waiting for him in this world.

51:34.500 --> 51:37.500
That is, what events are happening here,

51:37.500 --> 51:41.500
and can predict what will happen in a while.

51:41.500 --> 51:43.500
Based on this postulate,

51:43.500 --> 51:45.500
Kelly emphasizes once again,

51:45.500 --> 51:48.500
and this is the result of this main postulate,

51:48.500 --> 51:52.500
that the existence of a person is, first of all,

51:52.500 --> 51:55.500
a cognitive, that is, a cognitive process.

51:55.500 --> 52:01.500
Any behavior of a person, any action, any approach,

52:01.500 --> 52:03.500
is a learning.

52:03.500 --> 52:07.500
If we are in a familiar environment,

52:07.500 --> 52:10.500
where it becomes boring,

52:10.500 --> 52:13.500
we have a reason for development.

52:13.500 --> 52:17.500
What will happen if something changes?

52:17.500 --> 52:20.500
For example, one lamp went out today,

52:20.500 --> 52:23.500
tomorrow it will be the second, the third.

52:23.500 --> 52:26.500
How many lamps can remain

52:26.500 --> 52:29.500
to be able to work?

52:31.500 --> 52:38.500
Accordingly, a person begins to learn the world,

52:38.500 --> 52:43.500
to create an environment of learning,

52:43.500 --> 52:48.500
even in the conditions when there is nothing to learn.

52:48.500 --> 52:52.500
And this is a normal adaptive mechanism.

52:52.500 --> 52:56.500
It is better to predict than to be unprepared

52:56.500 --> 52:59.500
for the changes that will happen.

52:59.500 --> 53:05.500
Kelly assumes that the learning of the world around him

53:06.500 --> 53:11.500
is happening in the process of modeling this world.

53:11.500 --> 53:14.500
And modeling in the broadest sense of the word.

53:14.500 --> 53:17.500
This is not the modeling that Bandura has.

53:17.500 --> 53:20.500
When there is a model,

53:20.500 --> 53:23.500
and we try to learn,

53:23.500 --> 53:26.500
to achieve the same results as this model.

53:26.500 --> 53:29.500
Under the modeling, Kelly understands

53:29.500 --> 53:33.500
the construction of a cognitive map of the whole world.

53:33.500 --> 53:36.500
This is the modeling of another person.

53:36.500 --> 53:39.500
This is the construction of predictions

53:39.500 --> 53:42.500
about what will happen in this world.

53:42.500 --> 53:45.500
This is the reflection on what I want to achieve,

53:45.500 --> 53:47.500
why I need it,

53:47.500 --> 53:50.500
whether it is worth working for me,

53:50.500 --> 53:53.500
where and how to work, what to do.

53:53.500 --> 53:57.500
In fact, this is a selection of different alternative options.

53:57.500 --> 54:00.500
The more alternative options I have selected,

54:00.500 --> 54:03.500
the more opportunities I can choose.

54:03.500 --> 54:06.500
The more I have a choice,

54:06.500 --> 54:10.500
the more opportunities I have to predict

54:10.500 --> 54:14.500
what I have not yet encountered.

54:14.500 --> 54:18.500
This is why the Kelly cognitive mechanisms are needed.

54:18.500 --> 54:22.500
It should be said that the personal constructs

54:22.500 --> 54:25.500
that are in a person's head

54:25.500 --> 54:29.500
are not autonomous elements.

54:29.500 --> 54:32.500
What we were talking about

54:32.500 --> 54:35.500
when we were considering the construction

54:35.500 --> 54:38.500
of cognitive-behavioral theories,

54:38.500 --> 54:41.500
that everything is tied to the system,

54:41.500 --> 54:44.500
finds its bright embodiment in Kelly.

54:44.500 --> 54:47.500
All personal constructs are tied to each other.

54:47.500 --> 54:52.500
Of course, if we understand business well,

54:52.500 --> 54:56.500
then the corresponding information

54:57.500 --> 55:02.500
is quickly associated with the existing information,

55:02.500 --> 55:05.500
compared to what we know,

55:05.500 --> 55:08.500
and analyzed as what is new in this information.

55:08.500 --> 55:12.500
In this case, it turns out that we acquire knowledge

55:12.500 --> 55:16.500
that is built into the existing system.

55:16.500 --> 55:19.500
In this regard, if we encounter

55:19.500 --> 55:22.500
absolutely new knowledge,

55:22.500 --> 55:27.500
then it is very difficult to find its place in what we know.

55:27.500 --> 55:30.500
This is a very important task.

55:30.500 --> 55:33.500
Why, for example, with age,

55:33.500 --> 55:36.500
it becomes harder and harder to learn?

55:36.500 --> 55:39.500
The fact is that the more we live,

55:39.500 --> 55:42.500
the more experience we gain.

55:42.500 --> 55:45.500
Therefore, when we learn something new,

55:45.500 --> 55:49.500
there is a need to associate it with what we already know.

55:49.500 --> 55:54.500
We are constantly trying to find the connection between elements.

55:54.500 --> 55:57.500
This is where conservatism comes from,

55:57.500 --> 56:00.500
rigidity comes from,

56:00.500 --> 56:03.500
creativity comes from.

56:03.500 --> 56:07.500
It all depends on how we treat our cognitive map.

56:07.500 --> 56:10.500
Do we consider it given and true,

56:10.500 --> 56:13.500
because it has helped me for 40 years

56:13.500 --> 56:16.500
and there has been no cut,

56:16.500 --> 56:19.500
or am I always ready to change it

56:19.500 --> 56:22.500
because I know that the world is constantly changing

56:22.500 --> 56:25.500
and I need to be ready for this change?

56:25.500 --> 56:28.500
We cannot impose a rigid scheme on the world.

56:28.500 --> 56:31.500
Again, Kelly comes from the fact

56:31.500 --> 56:35.500
that the result of interacting with the world

56:35.500 --> 56:40.500
is the formation of one's own cognitive network.

56:40.500 --> 56:43.500
The goal of interacting with the world

56:43.500 --> 56:46.500
is to build a cognitive map of this world,

56:46.500 --> 56:49.500
that is, to learn about this world.

56:49.500 --> 56:52.500
The more I learn about this world,

56:52.500 --> 56:56.500
the more I become connected to personal constructs,

56:56.500 --> 56:59.500
the more I have connections between them,

56:59.500 --> 57:06.500
and the more changes I am ready to consider.

57:06.500 --> 57:10.500
Kelly emphasizes that all personal constructs

57:11.500 --> 57:14.500
