or other ways to compensate for the problems

01:05:50.500 --> 01:05:53.500
and, accordingly, these are the people

01:05:53.500 --> 01:05:56.500
we can form a staff reserve.

01:05:56.500 --> 01:05:59.500
These are the people who can work

01:05:59.500 --> 01:06:02.500
as mentors of new managers,

01:06:02.500 --> 01:06:05.500
new specialists.

01:06:05.500 --> 01:06:08.500
These are the people who are the guides

01:06:08.500 --> 01:06:11.500
and bearers of corporate history.

01:06:11.500 --> 01:06:14.500
After all, every company is proud

01:06:14.500 --> 01:06:17.500
of the history it has.

01:06:17.500 --> 01:06:20.500
The company without history

01:06:20.500 --> 01:06:23.500
is not a company.

01:06:23.500 --> 01:06:26.500
In this regard, organizational training

01:06:26.500 --> 01:06:29.500
has two functions.

01:06:29.500 --> 01:06:32.500
On the one hand, it solves purely educational tasks,

01:06:32.500 --> 01:06:35.500
teaching, forming the missing skills,

01:06:35.500 --> 01:06:38.500
sharpening, developing the skills

01:06:38.500 --> 01:06:41.500
that are present.

01:06:41.500 --> 01:06:44.500
On the other hand, organizational training

01:06:44.500 --> 01:06:47.500
is a way of uniting,

01:06:47.500 --> 01:06:50.500
developing, and further changes

01:06:50.500 --> 01:06:53.500
in the organization that exists.

01:06:53.500 --> 01:06:56.500
It is a way of carrying out missions

01:06:56.500 --> 01:06:59.500
to other employees of the organization,

01:06:59.500 --> 01:07:02.500
exchanging opinions, and analyzing the situation.

01:07:02.500 --> 01:07:05.500
It is a way of building communication

01:07:05.500 --> 01:07:08.500
and interaction with subsequent motivation,

01:07:08.500 --> 01:07:11.500
with subsequent assessment of employees

01:07:11.500 --> 01:07:14.500
and the tasks that the organization has.

01:07:14.500 --> 01:07:17.500
It is a way of showing the relationship

01:07:17.500 --> 01:07:20.500
with the employee that the organization

01:07:20.500 --> 01:07:23.500
is interested in the people who work there,

01:07:23.500 --> 01:07:26.500
and the organization is ready to provide them

01:07:26.500 --> 01:07:29.500
with conditions for further development.

01:07:29.500 --> 01:07:32.500
When we talked about individual training,

01:07:32.500 --> 01:07:35.500
we considered the main criteria of individual training.

01:07:35.500 --> 01:07:38.500
Let's do the same from the point of view

01:07:38.500 --> 01:07:41.500
of organizational training.

01:07:41.500 --> 01:07:44.500
The difference is that if individual training

01:07:44.500 --> 01:07:47.500
is a traditional problem that has existed

01:07:47.500 --> 01:07:50.500
for more than a decade,

01:07:50.500 --> 01:07:53.500
then organizational training is a new approach

01:07:53.500 --> 01:07:56.500
that has developed and is getting

01:07:56.500 --> 01:07:59.500
more and more widespread in organizations.

01:07:59.500 --> 01:08:02.500
Accordingly, the problems, tasks,

01:08:02.500 --> 01:08:05.500
and criteria that arise from the point of view

01:08:05.500 --> 01:08:08.500
of the coverage of a particular problem

01:08:08.500 --> 01:08:11.500
are even more controversial than the criteria

01:08:11.500 --> 01:08:14.500
that we talked about in the case of individual training.

01:08:14.500 --> 01:08:17.500
However, our task is to get a basic idea

01:08:17.500 --> 01:08:20.500
of the advantages and the underlying

01:08:20.500 --> 01:08:23.500
elements of organizational training,

01:08:23.500 --> 01:08:26.500
because organizational training is a huge investment.

01:08:26.500 --> 01:08:29.500
First, it is a means of organization,

01:08:29.500 --> 01:08:32.500
and secondly, it is a time-consuming process.

01:08:32.500 --> 01:08:35.500
The fact is that organizational training

01:08:35.500 --> 01:08:38.500
is not the kind of training that is carried out

01:08:38.500 --> 01:08:41.500
with a three-time production.

01:08:41.500 --> 01:08:44.500
In fact, it includes a week or two months,

01:08:44.500 --> 01:08:47.500
and most of the employees,

01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:50.500
and the leading employees,

01:08:50.500 --> 01:08:53.500
are disconnected from the direct activity.

01:08:53.500 --> 01:08:56.500
And again, the same dilemma arises.

01:08:56.500 --> 01:08:59.500
Where is this golden mean?

01:09:00.500 --> 01:09:03.500
What should be the duration of this training?

01:09:03.500 --> 01:09:06.500
What should be the return of this training?

01:09:06.500 --> 01:09:09.500
What should be the investment in this training?

01:09:09.500 --> 01:09:12.500
If I have now disconnected my employees

01:09:12.500 --> 01:09:15.500
from their direct activity for a month,

01:09:15.500 --> 01:09:18.500
how quickly will I, first of all,

01:09:18.500 --> 01:09:21.500
recover the lost benefit that they did not receive,

01:09:21.500 --> 01:09:24.500
and secondly, what additional profit

01:09:24.500 --> 01:09:27.500
will it give me in order to pay off my investments?

01:09:28.500 --> 01:09:31.500
When we talk about organizational training,

01:09:31.500 --> 01:09:34.500
the first question that arises is

01:09:34.500 --> 01:09:37.500
the way of its organization.

01:09:37.500 --> 01:09:40.500
What should be the concentration of participants?

01:09:40.500 --> 01:09:43.500
How best to conduct organizational training?

01:09:43.500 --> 01:09:46.500
Individually.

01:09:46.500 --> 01:09:49.500
That is, there are employees of the organization,

01:09:49.500 --> 01:09:52.500
I release them from work,

01:09:52.500 --> 01:09:55.500
and then invited specialists

01:09:56.500 --> 01:09:59.500
to conduct group training.

01:09:59.500 --> 01:10:02.500
How to make groups?

01:10:02.500 --> 01:10:05.500
And which employees should be included?

01:10:05.500 --> 01:10:08.500
One rank, different ranks, experienced,

01:10:08.500 --> 01:10:11.500
beginners, is it worth mixing groups?

01:10:11.500 --> 01:10:14.500
Will everyone be interested in this group?

01:10:14.500 --> 01:10:17.500
Again, how much will it pay off?

01:10:17.500 --> 01:10:20.500
Will the beginners be able to take that experience

01:10:20.500 --> 01:10:23.500
and not miss the opportunity

01:10:23.500 --> 01:10:26.500
to get a profit?

01:10:26.500 --> 01:10:29.500
Will experienced managers look up to the beginners

01:10:29.500 --> 01:10:32.500
and not consider it a waste of time

01:10:32.500 --> 01:10:35.500
when they could implement the plan

01:10:35.500 --> 01:10:38.500
and get a profit?

01:10:38.500 --> 01:10:41.500
If we talk about the training of the organization in general,

01:10:41.500 --> 01:10:44.500
what levels of employees should be trained?

01:10:44.500 --> 01:10:47.500
We cannot, even with all the desire of everyone,

01:10:47.500 --> 01:10:50.500
train all the employees,

01:10:50.500 --> 01:10:53.500
we live in a very tough business environment.

01:10:53.500 --> 01:10:56.500
Accordingly, if you achieve some results,

01:10:56.500 --> 01:10:59.500
you need to continue to achieve and develop them,

01:10:59.500 --> 01:11:02.500
because there are always those competitors

01:11:02.500 --> 01:11:05.500
who come to us on our heels.

01:11:05.500 --> 01:11:08.500
Again, how should the training be concentrated?

01:11:08.500 --> 01:11:11.500
How to do it optimally?

01:11:11.500 --> 01:11:14.500
From the point of view of the organization,

01:11:14.500 --> 01:11:17.500
how to make it more efficient?

01:11:17.500 --> 01:11:20.500
How to do it optimally from the point of view

01:11:20.500 --> 01:11:23.500
of the budget economy and the result?

01:11:23.500 --> 01:11:26.500
Everything is the same as we talked about

01:11:26.500 --> 01:11:29.500
in the case of individual training,

01:11:29.500 --> 01:11:32.500
only there was no such task,

01:11:32.500 --> 01:11:35.500
there we sent employees.

01:11:35.500 --> 01:11:38.500
We immediately build training within our organization.

01:11:38.500 --> 01:11:41.500
The next problem that is connected with the same problems

01:11:41.500 --> 01:11:44.500
that were in the case of individual training

01:11:44.500 --> 01:11:47.500
is that people working in the organization

01:11:47.500 --> 01:11:50.500
have different experiences,

01:11:50.500 --> 01:11:53.500
have different motivations,

01:11:53.500 --> 01:11:56.500
have different interests, have different tendencies.

01:11:56.500 --> 01:11:59.500
So, is it worth organizing training levels?

01:11:59.500 --> 01:12:02.500
How to distribute people at these levels?

01:12:02.500 --> 01:12:05.500
How to make training at each level

01:12:05.500 --> 01:12:08.500
contribute to the development of competence,

01:12:08.500 --> 01:12:11.500
skills, knowledge, specialization,

01:12:11.500 --> 01:12:14.500
so that they do not explain

01:12:14.500 --> 01:12:17.500
what they already know,

01:12:17.500 --> 01:12:20.500
what they already have,

01:12:20.500 --> 01:12:23.500
but to identify and diagnose

01:12:23.500 --> 01:12:26.500
what else to add to their skills

01:12:26.500 --> 01:12:29.500
so that they become even more productive

01:12:29.500 --> 01:12:32.500
and not only the company receives dividends

01:12:32.500 --> 01:12:35.500
from this, but also the company

01:12:35.500 --> 01:12:38.500
receives dividends from this.

01:12:38.500 --> 01:12:41.500
Not only the company receives dividends and profits from this,

01:12:41.500 --> 01:12:44.500
but also the employees themselves receive

01:12:44.500 --> 01:12:47.500
moral and material satisfaction from this

01:12:47.500 --> 01:12:50.500
in the form that the company invests in their training,

01:12:50.500 --> 01:12:53.500
which means that the company is interested in them,

01:12:53.500 --> 01:12:56.500
interested in their results,

01:12:56.500 --> 01:12:59.500
and, accordingly, the company does not treat them

01:12:59.500 --> 01:13:02.500
as a kind of screw to achieve its results.

01:13:02.500 --> 01:13:05.500
The next problem of organizational training

01:13:05.500 --> 01:13:08.500
that arises in this case

01:13:08.500 --> 01:13:11.500
is a problem of a large number of obstacles

01:13:11.500 --> 01:13:14.500
that arise from the point of view

01:13:14.500 --> 01:13:17.500
of the productivity of learning.

01:13:17.500 --> 01:13:20.500
The fact is that learning

01:13:20.500 --> 01:13:23.500
significantly implies mastering new skills,

01:13:23.500 --> 01:13:26.500
and here a very pinching problem arises.

01:13:26.500 --> 01:13:29.500
An experienced manager who was sent to train,

01:13:29.500 --> 01:13:32.500
who has completed this training,

01:13:32.500 --> 01:13:35.500
can consider this training

01:13:35.500 --> 01:13:38.500
as a dissatisfaction of the management,

01:13:38.500 --> 01:13:41.500
its direct boss, with its results.

01:13:41.500 --> 01:13:44.500
After all, if the management is satisfied

01:13:44.500 --> 01:13:47.500
with these results, why am I being fired

01:13:47.500 --> 01:13:50.500
from my job so that I study for God knows what?

01:13:50.500 --> 01:13:53.500
The problem is very serious

01:13:53.500 --> 01:13:56.500
because in any organization we work with living people,

01:13:56.500 --> 01:13:59.500
with their ambitions,

01:13:59.500 --> 01:14:02.500
with their expectations,

01:14:02.500 --> 01:14:05.500
with their values.

01:14:05.500 --> 01:14:08.500
Remember everything we talked about

01:14:08.500 --> 01:14:11.500
when considering the approach of Bandura

01:14:11.500 --> 01:14:14.500
and when considering the cognitive-ambivarial approach of Rotter.

01:14:14.500 --> 01:14:17.500
People have motives,

01:14:17.500 --> 01:14:20.500
people have aspirations,

01:14:20.500 --> 01:14:23.500
people have clings, people have ambitions,

01:14:23.500 --> 01:14:26.500
and it may turn out that the management

01:14:26.500 --> 01:14:29.500
organizes this process with the best motivations,

01:14:29.500 --> 01:14:32.500
with the best expectations,

01:14:32.500 --> 01:14:35.500
and the employees perceive it

01:14:35.500 --> 01:14:38.500
as distrust of themselves.

01:14:38.500 --> 01:14:41.500
Moreover, they even begin to look for new jobs

01:14:41.500 --> 01:14:44.500
where they seem to be in demand.

01:14:44.500 --> 01:14:47.500
If we train what is called star managers

01:14:47.500 --> 01:14:50.500
who are successful in their field,

01:14:50.500 --> 01:14:53.500
then there is a problem of losing valuable personnel.

01:14:54.500 --> 01:14:57.500
How to motivate people to study?

01:14:57.500 --> 01:15:00.500
How to justify and how to offer

01:15:00.500 --> 01:15:03.500
these or those forms of organizational interaction

01:15:03.500 --> 01:15:06.500
so that people do not perceive it

01:15:06.500 --> 01:15:09.500
as a dissatisfaction

01:15:09.500 --> 01:15:12.500
or as a meaningless waste of time?

01:15:15.500 --> 01:15:18.500
And, of course, the next problem

01:15:18.500 --> 01:15:21.500
that arises is related to the fact

01:15:22.500 --> 01:15:25.500
that organizational training is a very serious interference

01:15:25.500 --> 01:15:28.500
in the functioning of the organization.

01:15:28.500 --> 01:15:31.500
It is a very serious interference

01:15:31.500 --> 01:15:34.500
in the organizational behavior

01:15:34.500 --> 01:15:37.500
that we have discussed.

01:15:37.500 --> 01:15:40.500
The fact is that there are certain relationships,

01:15:40.500 --> 01:15:43.500
certain communications,

01:15:43.500 --> 01:15:46.500
certain norms, certain traditions

01:15:46.500 --> 01:15:49.500
that are considered to be self-evident in the organization.

01:15:50.500 --> 01:15:53.500
There is no question of why they are like that.

01:15:53.500 --> 01:15:56.500
It is accepted.

01:15:56.500 --> 01:15:59.500
And suddenly, when organizational training is going on,

01:15:59.500 --> 01:16:02.500
it becomes clear that it is not necessary

01:16:02.500 --> 01:16:05.500
to talk about it.

01:16:05.500 --> 01:16:08.500
Qualitative training is the training

01:16:08.500 --> 01:16:11.500
that makes managers think about the prospects

01:16:11.500 --> 01:16:14.500
of the development of their organization.

01:16:14.500 --> 01:16:17.500
We will talk about this in more detail

01:16:18.500 --> 01:16:21.500
in the next lecture.

01:16:21.500 --> 01:16:24.500
So, the question arises,

01:16:24.500 --> 01:16:27.500
why do we do it this way and not the other way around?

01:16:27.500 --> 01:16:30.500
A lot of negative things

01:16:30.500 --> 01:16:33.500
that exist in the organization

01:16:33.500 --> 01:16:36.500
begin to be identified and recorded.

01:16:36.500 --> 01:16:39.500
And there is a negative in any organization

01:16:39.500 --> 01:16:42.500
simply because if there are a lot of people

01:16:42.500 --> 01:16:45.500
working in the organization,

01:16:45.500 --> 01:16:48.500
the employees are always dissatisfied with something.

01:16:48.500 --> 01:16:51.500
Either with the salary,

01:16:51.500 --> 01:16:54.500
or with the motivation, or with the relations.

01:16:54.500 --> 01:16:57.500
And in this regard,

01:16:57.500 --> 01:17:00.500
any interference

01:17:00.500 --> 01:17:03.500
brings very dangerous and fraught moments.

01:17:03.500 --> 01:17:06.500
And then the question arises,

01:17:06.500 --> 01:17:09.500
the interference will still be there.

01:17:09.500 --> 01:17:12.500
How to make it effective

01:17:12.500 --> 01:17:15.500
and how to reduce it to zero?

01:17:15.500 --> 01:17:18.500
All possible difficulties will arise.

01:17:18.500 --> 01:17:21.500
They will arise for sure.

01:17:21.500 --> 01:17:24.500
These are the main problems

01:17:24.500 --> 01:17:27.500
that arise in the concept of organizational training.

01:17:27.500 --> 01:17:30.500
If we read the literature

01:17:30.500 --> 01:17:33.500
that is being published on this topic,

01:17:33.500 --> 01:17:36.500
there are a lot of smaller problems.

01:17:36.500 --> 01:17:39.500
There are specific examples

01:17:39.500 --> 01:17:42.500
of the difficulties that arise in organizational training.

01:17:42.500 --> 01:17:45.500
In this regard,

01:17:45.500 --> 01:17:48.500
the question arises,

01:17:48.500 --> 01:17:51.500
what arguments prevail

01:17:51.500 --> 01:17:54.500
for the concept of organizational training?

01:17:54.500 --> 01:17:57.500
If this form of training

01:17:57.500 --> 01:18:00.500
becomes more and more popular

01:18:00.500 --> 01:18:03.500
in foreign companies,

01:18:03.500 --> 01:18:06.500
it is the best indicator

01:18:06.500 --> 01:18:09.500
that the advantages that are obtained

01:18:09.500 --> 01:18:12.500
are a significant argument

01:18:12.500 --> 01:18:15.500
for the transition

01:18:15.500 --> 01:18:18.500
from individual training

01:18:18.500 --> 01:18:21.500
to organizational training.

01:18:21.500 --> 01:18:24.500
But this is a qualitative change

01:18:24.500 --> 01:18:27.500
that arises in relation to the organization,

01:18:27.500 --> 01:18:30.500
to the staff,

01:18:30.500 --> 01:18:33.500
and to the organization of all the types of training

01:18:33.500 --> 01:18:36.500
that exist now.

01:18:36.500 --> 01:18:39.500
What types of organizational training exist?

01:18:39.500 --> 01:18:42.500
Types of training

01:18:42.500 --> 01:18:45.500
differ in the goals and forms

01:18:45.500 --> 01:18:48.500
that can be identified.

01:18:48.500 --> 01:18:51.500
Of course, these types of training

01:18:51.500 --> 01:18:54.500
are closely interlinked with individual training,

01:18:54.500 --> 01:18:57.500
but when it comes to individual training,

01:18:57.500 --> 01:19:00.500
to a large extent,

01:19:00.500 --> 01:19:03.500
it is connected with the individual features

01:19:03.500 --> 01:19:06.500
of one person, one employee,

01:19:06.500 --> 01:19:09.500
one manager who works in the organization.

01:19:09.500 --> 01:19:12.500
When we talk about organizational training,

01:19:12.500 --> 01:19:15.500
there are any difficulties,

01:19:15.500 --> 01:19:18.500
misunderstandings that arise

01:19:18.500 --> 01:19:21.500
that are associated

01:19:21.500 --> 01:19:24.500
with the problems arising in any organization.

01:19:24.500 --> 01:19:27.500
Usually, there are three types of training.

01:19:27.500 --> 01:19:30.500
The first type of training is adaptive training.

01:19:30.500 --> 01:19:33.500
Its goal is to develop abilities,

01:19:33.500 --> 01:19:36.500
develop skills,

01:19:36.500 --> 01:19:39.500
develop competencies,

01:19:39.500 --> 01:19:42.500
understand new situations

01:19:42.500 --> 01:19:45.500
that may arise in business.

01:19:45.500 --> 01:19:48.500
This is a preliminary,

01:19:48.500 --> 01:19:51.500
prognostic training.

01:19:51.500 --> 01:19:54.500
Business is constantly developing forward.

01:19:54.500 --> 01:19:57.500
It is a constant change,

01:19:57.500 --> 01:20:00.500
and you need to be ready for these changes.

01:20:00.500 --> 01:20:03.500
If you are stagnant,

01:20:03.500 --> 01:20:06.500
then, in fact,

01:20:06.500 --> 01:20:09.500
you are talking about a very unfavorable perspective.

01:20:09.500 --> 01:20:12.500
As for adaptive training,

01:20:12.500 --> 01:20:15.500
from one point of view,

01:20:15.500 --> 01:20:18.500
this is perhaps the most familiar form of training,

01:20:18.500 --> 01:20:21.500
because we adapt each employee

01:20:21.500 --> 01:20:24.500
to a new place,

01:20:24.500 --> 01:20:27.500
to a new purpose,

01:20:27.500 --> 01:20:30.500
to a new function,

01:20:30.500 --> 01:20:33.500
to a new plan.

01:20:33.500 --> 01:20:36.500
If we change some fundamental points,

01:20:36.500 --> 01:20:39.500
enter a new market sphere,

01:20:39.500 --> 01:20:42.500
strive to change the strategic conditions

01:20:42.500 --> 01:20:45.500
of the organization's development,

01:20:45.500 --> 01:20:48.500
we must prepare and adapt the organization's staff

01:20:48.500 --> 01:20:51.500
to the new visions that are introduced in the organization.

01:20:51.500 --> 01:20:54.500
In fact, adaptive training

01:20:54.500 --> 01:20:57.500
is a necessary training

01:20:57.500 --> 01:21:00.500
to successfully solve

01:21:00.500 --> 01:21:03.500
and meet new requirements

01:21:03.500 --> 01:21:06.500
that may arise.

01:21:06.500 --> 01:21:09.500
Another type of training is generative training.

01:21:09.500 --> 01:21:12.500
As for generative training,

01:21:12.500 --> 01:21:15.500
in fact,

01:21:15.500 --> 01:21:18.500
it is a training that requires

01:21:18.500 --> 01:21:21.500
the development of the ability to look at your organization in a new way,

01:21:21.500 --> 01:21:24.500
its prospects,

01:21:24.500 --> 01:21:27.500
its place on the market,

01:21:27.500 --> 01:21:30.500
its relationship with competitors.

01:21:30.500 --> 01:21:33.500
In fact, it is a creative training.

01:21:33.500 --> 01:21:36.500
In this case,

01:21:36.500 --> 01:21:39.500
it is about changing some of the organizational systems,

01:21:39.500 --> 01:21:42.500
some basic principles,

01:21:42.500 --> 01:21:45.500
